# ${title}

This page stress-tests the wiki-link parser by embedding many
``[[wiki-style]]`` links alongside ordinary markup. A realistic
encyclopedia-style page tends to have several dozen wiki links per
screen of content.

## References to other pages

The [[Planet]] [[Earth]] orbits the star [[Sun]] in the
[[Solar System]], which itself is part of the [[Milky Way]] galaxy.
Earth's natural satellite is the [[Moon]], and it has two neighbors:
[[Venus]] inward and [[Mars]] outward. Further out lie [[Jupiter]],
[[Saturn]], [[Uranus]], and [[Neptune]].

Nearby stars include [[Proxima Centauri]], [[Alpha Centauri]],
[[Barnard's Star]], [[Wolf 359]], [[Sirius]], [[Epsilon Eridani]],
[[Tau Ceti]], and [[61 Cygni]]. The nearest galactic group contains
[[Andromeda Galaxy]], the [[Triangulum Galaxy]], and several
satellite galaxies of the [[Milky Way]] itself.

